November 9th in Class: Election Maps

Duncan Hook, Andrew McLain, Aryan Khorram

2020-11-10

library(tidyverse)
library(openintro)
library(albersusa)
election_state <- read_csv("elections.csv")
election_county <- read_csv("election_county.csv")

my_map_theme <- function(){
theme(panel.background=element_blank(),
axis.text=element_blank(),
axis.ticks=element_blank(),
axis.title=element_blank())
}

us_states <- usa_sf()
us_county <- counties_sf()

Exercise 1

my_cutpoints <- c(-100,-15,-5,-1,0,1,5,15,100)
my_labels <- c("R+15 or more", "R+5 to R+15", "R+1 to R+5", "R+0 to R+1",
"D+0 to D+1", "D+1 to D+5", "D+5 to D+15", "D+15 or more")

my_colors <- c("#b2182b","#d6604d","#f4a582","#fddbc7",
"#d1e5f0","#92c5de","#4393c3","#2166ac")


election_state <- election_state %>%
rename('2012' = d_points_2012,
       '2016' = d_points) %>%
  pivot_longer(c('2012','2016'), names_to="Year",
               values_to='dpoints')

election_state_2012_2016 <- us_states %>%
left_join(election_state, c("name"="state")) %>%
mutate(margin = cut(dpoints, breaks = my_cutpoints, labels = my_labels))

ggplot(election_state_2012_2016) +
geom_sf(aes(fill=margin)) +
facet_wrap(~Year, nrow = 2) +
my_map_theme() +
scale_fill_manual("", values = my_colors) +
theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size=15)) +
theme(plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

Exercise 2

election_county <- election_county %>%
  mutate(dpoints = ((votes_dem_2016-votes_gop_2016)/total_votes_2016)*100)

us_county <- mutate(us_county, fips2 = as.numeric(as.character(fips)))

election_county_2016 <- us_county %>%
left_join(election_county, c("fips2"="fips", "iso_3166_2" = "state")) %>%
mutate(margin = cut(dpoints, breaks = my_cutpoints, labels = my_labels))


ggplot(election_county_2016) +
geom_sf(aes(fill=margin)) +
my_map_theme() +
scale_fill_manual("", values = my_colors) +
geom_sf(data = us_states, alpha=0, size=.5, color="black") +
theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size=15)) +
theme(plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

county_wa <- election_county_2016 %>%
 filter(state == "Washington")

ggplot(county_wa) +
geom_sf(aes(fill=margin)) +
my_map_theme() +
scale_fill_manual("", values = my_colors) +
theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size=15)) +
theme(plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5))

west_us <- election_county_2016 %>%
  filter(census_region == "West")

west_states <- usa_sf() %>% 
  filter(iso_3166_2%in%c("WA", "OR", "ID", "CA", 
                         "NV", "AZ", "UT", "MT", 
                         "WY", "CO", "NM", "AK", 
                         "HI"))

ggplot(west_us) +
geom_sf(aes(fill=margin)) +
my_map_theme() +
geom_sf(data = west_states, alpha=0, size=.5, color="black") +
scale_fill_manual("", values = my_colors) +
theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5, size=15)) +
theme(plot.subtitle = element_text(hjust = 0.5))
